two collections.

both contain numbers, numbers ordered smallest to largest.

i want to find the median if the collections were combined and sorted.

i want to do this in log(n) time.

which means every step, i half the input size.

what does the median look like?

it's a number, or the average of two numbers.

three scenarios:
    a number, it exists in one collection.
    two numbers, they exist in each collection.
    two numbers, they exist in one collection.